First Lady Michelle Obama will host a preview of the 2015 holiday decor at the White House on December 2, 2015. She will deliver remarks in the East Room and then be joined by White House Executive Chef Cris Comerford, White House Executive Pastry Chef Susan Morrison, and White House Chief Floral Designer Roshan Ghaffarian in the State Dining Room. They will demonstrate holiday crafts and treats. The event will also welcome military families as part of the Joining Forces initiative, with many of the decorations honoring military families.